---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout title="Terms of Service - LocalResizer" description="Terms of service for LocalResizer, a browser-based static image processing tool.">
  <article class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-16 prose prose-slate">
    <h1>Terms of Service</h1>
    <p><em>Last updated: March 2026</em></p>
    <h2>Acceptance</h2>
    <p>By using LocalResizer, you agree to these terms. If you do not agree, please do not use the site.</p>
    <h2>Service Description</h2>
    <p>LocalResizer provides browser-based tools for static image compression and resizing. The current scope covers JPEG, PNG, and WebP workflows.</p>
    <p>The current public release includes homepage quick tools, target-size pages, and exact canvas pages for the live YouTube artwork workflows.</p>
    <h2>Usage</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>The site is provided as-is without warranties of any kind</li>
      <li>You are responsible for the files you choose to process</li>
      <li>You must not use the site for unlawful activity</li>
      <li>We may revise the site or its feature scope over time</li>
    </ul>
    <h2>Output Expectations</h2>
    <p>Target-size workflows are best-effort because final file size depends on the source image. Exact canvas pages guarantee the output dimensions of the canvas, but may add padding to keep the whole image visible without distortion.</p>
    <h2>Intellectual Property</h2>
    <p>You retain your rights to the files you process. We do not claim ownership of your images.</p>
    <h2>Limitation of Liability</h2>
    <p>We are not liable for losses arising from use of the site, including unexpected output quality, failed processing, or file compatibility issues.</p>
    <h2>Contact</h2>
    <p>Questions about these terms? Visit the <a href="/contact">contact page</a>.</p>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
